children.html:
Banksy sets up a stall in Central Park selling signed original stencil artwork. 
        But forgets to tell his publicist...

With this work, Banksy demonstrates an artist is really just a brand.
        The same authentic Banksy works would be sold in auctions for hundreds of thousands of dollars.
        But here, pedestrians ignore that they're buying real Banksys, 
        and therefore try to barter for a few dollars discount.
